      "message": "It is now possible to reach UnhandledExceptionHandler() with StartHandlerProcess() having failed, or with StartHandlerProcess() running or to-be-run but with the possibility that it will fail.\n\nWhat happens? It looks like we wind up hitting the minute-long sleep. Not too great.\n\nIt looks like we need a way to synchronize this with the completion of StartHandlerProcess() (if it was called), successful or not, and bail out without the SetEvent() or Sleep() if it was unsuccessful.",
